About
Top of the Rock Observation Deck, the newly opened, 3-tiered observation deck on the 67th, 69th and 70th floors of 30 Rockefeller Plaza, is New York City's most amazing attraction! The unforgettable experience includes a panoramic 360-degree, unobstructed view from the 70th floor observatory, 850 feet in the sky! Hours of Operation: 8:00 AM - Midnight, last elevator goes up at 11:00 PM.Main entrance is located on 50th Street between 5th & 6th Avenues.
Duration: 1-2 hours

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Midtown
This is the iconic New York that so many visitors imagine before they visit - spectacular skyscrapers like the Chrysler Building and Empire State Building, iconic public buildings like Grand Central Terminal and the New York Public Library, and the non-stop hustle and bustle of the city streets. Fifth Avenue is a shopper's paradise where you can find every kind of store imaginable, with fashion brands ranging from the affordable to the ultra-fancy. Visit Rockefeller Center to experience towering Art Deco grandeur, and foodies will love the busy restaurants that stay open late in Koreatown. After dark, Midtown calms down a bit, but at any time of day or night it still feels 100% New York.
How to get there
  • 47–50 Sts – Rockefeller Center • 2 min walk
  • 5th Ave / 53rd St • 5 min walk

roy1234
Canterbury, UK26 contributions
Great Views All Around
I really enjoyed this. You start from the bottom with a short film about the history and then in the Lift/ elevator it continues. At the top there are a couple of floors where you go out onto various balconies. And although this isnt the highest observation deck, you get some really good views South especially of the Empire State Building but the views North of Central Park are probably the best you get from any of the decks.
We paid for The Beam when we got to the top as we had a City Pass and therefore didn't go to the ticket booth at the bottom, which was handy for all of those with passes. The Beam itself doesn't last long but is a great photo opportunity and in my opinion, worth the money. For someone scared of heights, it could get the adrenaline pumping but it's safe as houses and i would still recommend it.
There is a café at the top but we didn't use it as we were pushed for time.
The gift shop on exit has some really good items reasonably priced as well.
Overall well worth doing.
Review of: Top of the Rock Observation Deck New York City Ticket
